%N A395679 Decimal expansion of the maximum width of a Reuleaux tetrahedron based on a tetrahedron with unit edge lengths.
%C A395679 The Reuleaux tetrahedron is not a solid of constant width: its maximum width is the distance between the midpoints of opposite edge arcs.
%H A395679 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A395679/b395679.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395679 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reuleaux_tetrahedron">Reuleaux tetrahedron</a>.
%H A395679 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A395679 Equals sqrt(3) - 1/sqrt(2) = A002194 - A010503.
%F A395679 Equals the smallest positive root of 4*x^4 - 28*x^2 + 25.
